<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>Moeketsi Mabote (60) from Bluegumbosch in QwaQwa said he can’t stop running as it’s his passion. “I jog from 6am to 11am almost every day,” he said.He said was busy training for the upcoming Soweto and Comrades marathons. “I’m not part of a club so I run at my own pace. I enjoy it because it’s my hunting ground for medals,” said Moeketsi. He started running marathons in 2012. The madala has won twelve medals so far and now runs as a veteran.He took the fifteenth spot in his age category in the 42,2km Marakele Marathon in Thabazimbi, Limpopo last month.His medals also include one for the Old Mutual Three Cranes Challenge in Harrismith, where he came third in the 32km race last year.He said his diet includes vegetables, fruit, milk and he makes sure he drinks plenty of water. His advice to budding runners is to take their exercise programme seriously because victory awaits them. He said his aim was to win a medal for an international race before he retires.